I previously had written something to fix this issue, however I removed it because I wasn't too sure if it was "proper" encoding for Python2 & 3.

I will push the commit after testing it a bit more, but this is what it looks like for now, all string values get passed to this encode function.

```python
    def _encode(self, value):
        # Encoding Value to for Python2/3 (default='utf-8')
        if value:
            if sys.version_info.major == 2:
                if isinstance(value, (str, unicode)):  # noqa
                    return value.encode('utf-8')

            elif sys.version_info.major == 3:
                if isinstance(value, str):
                    return value.encode('utf-8')
        return value
```

