Your method did work.  It went to the right vmhost.  However, the VM went to the root of the folder and not in the resource pool as expected.  

It seems that the resource pool found in vCenter (first hit) is not the right one since there will be multiple same resource pool names.  I was able to find the right one using the following code:

    for rp in vmhost.parent.resourcePool.resourcePool:
        if resourcepool:
            if rp.name == resourcepool:
                resource_pool = rp

However, I am wondering if there is a cleaner way to find the right resource pool for a particular host server.  Would I be able to leverage content.viewManager.CreateContainerView(content.rootFolder, vimtype, True) somehow?  If so, then I can use the sample get_obj function and pass the necessary parameters.  Can the content.rootFolder be changed to a particular host? 

I am new to all this so appreciate your patience.

